<h3>Hot Opinions</h3>
<p>I don't like numeric scores for a few reasons. They encourage people to not explain themselves and rely on the 
number as a good/bad indicator. They imply an objective rating to a subjective topic. They tend to raise 
unreasonable expectations. So I don't use them. Instead I will provide a tl;dr at the bottom of every review a
along with an emoticon that shows my feelings about what I reviewed. Overly positive reviews will have very happy
emoticons, negative ones will have negative emoticons. Easy to understand, and open to interpretation. Remember, 
these are just opinions ʕ´•ᴥ•`ʔ</p>
</section>
